column12: comment
char
A description of the dataset
Cruise name or travel name. Example : EGEE6 or PAST0601
Ship name. Example : Pourquoi Pas ?
Name of project which operates the TSG line. Example: SO-SSS
Ship call sign. Example : FABB
Ship MMSI (ASN) number. Example : 227 222 00
Date of TSG installation, format : yyyymmddDDHHMMSS
Thermosalinograph model number. Example : SBE21 or SBE45
Thermosalinograph serial number. Example: 2250
Date of TINT installation, format: yyyymmddHHMMSS
Temperature sensor at intake. Example: SBE38
Intake temperature sensor serial number. Example: 3940
Describe data type contained in file. Example: TRAJECTORY, PROFILE or TIME-SERIES
Indicate if the file contains real time or delayed mode data. R : real time data, D : delayed mode data
Sampling period in seconds: 6 to 3600
Date of first measurements (UTC), format: yyyymmddHHMMSS
Date of last measurements (UTC), format: yyyymmddHHMMSS
South limit of measurements
North limit of measurements
West limit of measurements
East limit of measurements
GOSUD file format version, example: 3.0
GOSUD NetCDF file format conventions, example: CF1.4, GOSUD 3.0
Date and time (UTC) of creation of this file, format: yyyymmddHHMMSS
Date and time (UTC) of update of this file, format: yyyymmddHHMMSS
Restriction on use for these data, example: NONE
This citation should be used for publications. Example : "These data were collected and made freely available by the International GOSUD Project and the national programmes that contribute to it."
Comment.

Model of water sample. Default: NA, Not Available, Example: OSIL
Description of navigation system. Example: GPS, GPS DIFFERENTIAL, ARGOS, INTERPOLATE, MANUAL, NONE, UNKNOW
